Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.57,0:01:34.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.94,0:01:41.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Death is nothing but a release,"\nmy friend once muttered to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.38,0:01:46.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"If death is a release, what is it\nthat you wish to give to them?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.49,0:01:49.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My friend answered\nme succinctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.86,0:01:54.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"I will give them eternal\nsuffering and remorse."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.06,0:01:59.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, I'm done with\nrunning away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:04.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know\nthe truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.43,0:02:08.44,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,352)}Act 22:\NCounterattack
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.15,0:02:19.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,General... Are you certain that\nwe are doing the right thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.35,0:02:22.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.26,0:02:27.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There has never been\nsuch a thing as "the truth"!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.59,0:02:32.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is something that you yourself create\nbased on your own convictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.33,0:02:35.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it means setting\naside our conscience...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:38.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and turning our weapons\non fellow soldiers, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.17,0:02:42.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,People don't look at\ntheir conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.97,0:02:46.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What they see is the truth that\nis standing there before them!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.68,0:02:51.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was the day before he... The day before Franz died.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.55,0:02:57.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That day, I walked all the way here\nafter you confessed your plans to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.36,0:02:59.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...my world turned\nupside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.33,0:03:03.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can still clearly remember how\nmy tears wouldn't stop flowing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.03,0:03:07.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...as I looked out onto\nthe sun-drenched river.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.33,0:03:13.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Franz... Franz gave some\nparting words to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:15.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said to never\nhate anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.01,0:03:18.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that feelings of love\nand feelings of hate...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.54,0:03:21.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...both start out as\ncaring about someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:30.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, please tell me! Tell me everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.10,0:03:43.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.30,0:03:47.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A toast to Edmond's last night\nof bachelorhood!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.52,0:04:04.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is Edmond Dantes\nin there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.59,0:04:08.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.00,0:04:13.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're here on General Morcerf's orders\nto collect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:17.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The General will soon be entering Paris.\NHe will form an interim government,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.84,0:04:21.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and we will see the birth of\NPresident Morcerf before the day is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:28.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take me with you. Take me to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:46.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why, that's... Fernand Mondego!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.57,0:04:54.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The National Assembly is hereby\nunder the control...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:56.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...of forces loyal to the Eastern Space Fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.74,0:05:00.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you lost your mind?!\NThis is an act of high treason!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:02.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We don't recognize your authority!\NWe don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:03.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.75,0:05:05.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your tongues.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.95,0:05:07.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.79,0:05:11.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The National Assembly\nis hereby dissolved!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:13.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I declare a state of\nmartial law in Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.73,0:05:21.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty-five years ago, I was a young man\nnamed Edmond Dantes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.13,0:05:25.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, before that day, I knew\nnothing of mistrusting others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.17,0:05:30.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I passed the days, praying for the\nhappiness of my father and fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.38,0:05:33.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond Dantes!\NYou are under arrest...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.61,0:05:37.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...as a prime suspect in the\nassassination of the Prince!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.38,0:05:38.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.32,0:05:39.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes! This is some sort\nof misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.95,0:05:43.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.99,0:05:46.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let go! Edmond!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.36,0:05:47.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.66,0:05:52.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've been charged\nwith a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.50,0:05:54.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.87,0:05:56.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We received an\nanonymous tip.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.10,0:06:00.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,According to the written accusation,\nyou have in your possession...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:03.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...a letter that reveals the plot behind\nthe assassination of the Prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.01,0:06:05.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world are you\ntalking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.24,0:06:10.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Before your captain died, I believe\nhe entrusted you with a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.55,0:06:14.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Captain's last request\nwas that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.85,0:06:17.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I deliver the letter to\nthe intended recipient.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.06,0:06:26.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Paris, Rue Coq-Heron, number 13.\NMonsieur Noirtier...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:32.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The letter contained the names of the men\ninvolved in the assassination plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:36.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Villefort's name was\nalso included within.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.34,0:06:43.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And I had unwittingly handed the letter over\nto the very person I shouldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.12,0:06:47.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You were simply carrying out\nyour duties faithfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.89,0:06:52.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dantes. Let me take care\nof this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.52,0:06:55.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that they'll be\nreleasing you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.29,0:06:57.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much, Monsieur Villefort!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.33,0:06:59.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can I ever\nthank you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.83,0:07:04.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My fiancée must be anxiously\nwaiting for me to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:10.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, have you spoken\nof this letter to anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.38,0:07:16.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, Monsieur. I obeyed the Captain's\nlast request and kept it secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:19.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No one else knows\nof this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:22.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:33.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here in Paris, it is believed\nto this day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.36,0:07:38.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that the Prince perished in an assassination\nplot orchestrated by enemies of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.17,0:07:42.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But the plot was devised\nby people from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.31,0:07:50.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those who had reaped enormous profits\nfrom the war wanted it to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.02,0:07:53.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.09,0:07:56.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,With the assassination, the\nworst possible outcome,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.35,0:07:58.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,prospects for peace became\na distant memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.19,0:08:02.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And just as those men wished,\nthe war spread,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:07.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...growing ever more intense in the name\nof avenging the assassination.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:14.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A-And one unlucky man\nwas consigned to oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.18,0:08:21.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those who had exploited me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.91,0:08:26.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...became prominent figures in\nthe financial and legal worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.78,0:08:31.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And the man who had climbed to\nthe very top of the military...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.56,0:08:35.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...eventually turned his eyes\nto the presidency.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.03,0:08:37.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is how\nit happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:40.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Call Monsieur Villefort!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.67,0:08:43.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What crime do they think I committed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.94,0:08:49.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't done anything! I'm... I'm innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.38,0:08:54.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What I found waiting for me when I was\nimprisoned within the Chateau d'lf...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:57.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...was the very embodiment\nof endless despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.65,0:09:02.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was an automated fortress on the frontier,\nbuilt to defend against unknown enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.82,0:09:06.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I became a component\nof its control system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:12.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In that place, that neverending Hell, I was\nnot even allowed the choice of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.41,0:09:27.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.35,0:09:30.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, kill me\nright now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.49,0:09:41.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't care about\nsalvation anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.99,0:09:46.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if my body\nshould disappear,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.06,0:09:51.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll find those who took\neverything away from me,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.44,0:09:55.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...those who drove me\nto ruin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.47,0:10:01.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and give them the cruelest, most\nmacabre punishment imaginable!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.38,0:10:08.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won't even give them the respite of death!\NWhat they'll get is eternal suffering!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.83,0:10:14.76,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.77,0:10:21.70,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.74,0:10:29.60,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:34.43,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hope... Grief...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.45,0:10:38.44,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Longing... Resignation...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.18,0:10:41.45,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Rage... Terror...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.05,0:10:45.78,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Despair... And then,\nhope once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:55.83,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For thousands of years, I have waited inside\nthis body for the arrival of a man like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.47,0:11:01.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.81,0:11:06.40,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.45,0:11:10.71,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you are\nwith me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.62,0:11:16.68,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To you, I give my knowledge\nand power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.12,0:11:21.42,gankutsuou,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And to me, you give your body\nand your spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:33.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert... I am the\NWheel of Fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:42.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, it is now only my unyielding,\nmerciless resolve which keeps me moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.29,0:11:52.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count! Even after everything that's happened,\NI don't want to let you leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.19,0:11:55.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to give up on\nyour revenge, Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.13,0:12:02.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Only one man may give an order\nto the Count of Monte Cristo,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.50,0:12:05.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and that is the Count of Monte Cristo himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.27,0:12:15.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, are you saying that there\nis no one left in your heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.01,0:12:21.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that the Count of Monte Cristo\nthat I knew no longer exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:34.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:46.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.01,0:12:52.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, stop this... Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:12:57.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Cabinet and National Assembly have ceded\nfull governing authority to the Space Forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.22,0:12:58.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Martial law has been declared!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:04.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Citizens are asked to surrender all weapons\nand refrain from venturing outdoors!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.16,0:13:07.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat, the Cabinet and\NNational Assembly have ceded...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.23,0:13:09.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...full governing authority\nto the Space Forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.47,0:13:10.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Martial law\nhas been declared!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.97,0:13:11.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My money! My money!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.60,0:13:14.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Citizens are asked\nto surrender all...\NMy money! My money!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.01,0:13:23.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well, what have\nwe here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.85,0:13:25.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's what it's\ncome to?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.19,0:13:30.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this how the\nworld works?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.02,0:13:34.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Off with your head!\NAnd yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:38.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Off with your head!\NI sentence you to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.54,0:13:54.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Baptistin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.65,0:13:57.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stand aside!\NI won't let you stop me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.89,0:14:02.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Take this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.29,0:14:05.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.06,0:14:09.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If anything happens, give us a shout.\NJust don't turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.50,0:14:16.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell the Count\nabout this, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.34,0:14:20.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Underground fortresses! Weapons depots!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.57,0:14:24.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a single one\nthat I don't know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:27.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to give them\na taste of my power!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.58,0:14:29.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.15,0:14:31.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your next target is the Arc de Triomphe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.12,0:14:38.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Spineless cowards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.29,0:15:13.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes! I've been waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.19,0:15:17.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Paris is finally\nkneeling before me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.30,0:15:23.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be what you wanted, Fernand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.20,0:15:30.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The dreams that you told me about\nwere full of hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.37,0:15:35.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But there IS hope! Listen, this pain\nis necessary for the good of the country!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.65,0:15:36.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fernand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.98,0:15:40.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're the First Lady now, Mercedes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.25,0:15:42.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to\nbe afraid of now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:48.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond is alive, and he's been\nright under our noses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.39,0:15:50.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.23,0:15:57.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The man who was once your best friend...\NThe man who was once my fiancée...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.80,0:16:03.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...has returned to us as the\NCount of Monte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.75,0:16:12.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He survived... But why now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.98,0:16:16.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That letter we received...\NSo that's what it was all about...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.66,0:16:19.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.06,0:16:24.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's come back to get\nhis revenge on us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.13,0:16:27.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Revenge? What are you\ntalking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.70,0:16:33.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and Edmond were best friends.\NWhat do you mean, revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.60,0:16:37.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Edmond want to\nget revenge against you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:43.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He and I... were\nbest friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.65,0:16:47.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I never once thought of that\nbastard as my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:49.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must have\nknown that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:51.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're always like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.09,0:16:55.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea how much\nthat naiveté of yours hurts people?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:17:02.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. The man who sent that letter\nthat got him arrested was ME!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:07.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't, he'd have been made the captain\nof a ship on the interplanetary shipping lanes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:11.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and I would've spent my entire life as\na menial laborer at the Marseilles docks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.84,0:17:15.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... I had to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.85,0:17:18.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?! It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.48,0:17:22.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your naiveté cast Edmond into\nthe depths of misery!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.16,0:17:34.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... I can't believe I said\nsuch horrible things to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.20,0:17:38.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry... Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.04,0:17:42.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes, I love you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:17:57.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.66,0:18:01.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's leave Paris together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.11,0:18:26.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've had it up to here with\nalways being the underdog!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.05,0:18:30.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of living in\nthat bastard's shadow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.22,0:18:33.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're staying here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.12,0:18:37.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to stay here\nby my side!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.83,0:18:44.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forget the time\nwe've spent together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.50,0:18:46.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.97,0:18:51.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Fernand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.81,0:18:57.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.38,0:19:01.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.75,0:19:03.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,MERCEDES!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.66,0:19:14.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.77,0:19:17.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother! Are you all right?! Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.37,0:19:18.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.04,0:19:23.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why did this\nhave to happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:27.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I loved her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:34.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And I loved you more\nthan anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.42,0:19:40.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.04,0:20:05.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet... I still have him to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:08.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.35,0:20:10.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.12,0:20:12.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.56,0:20:19.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:20.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eat this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.09,0:20:48.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.53,0:20:50.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You crazy kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.86,0:20:52.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Mondego?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.47,0:20:59.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This ain't good...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.70,0:21:02.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.47,0:21:09.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As long as he's still alive,\NI can't die, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.33,0:21:33.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monte Cristo!\NNo, Edmond Dantes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:38.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to take everything away from you,\njust as you did to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.77,0:23:12.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I continue to plead,\nas if praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.17,0:23:16.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To my father. To my mother.\NAnd most of all, to your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.47,0:23:19.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou, act 23...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.87,0:23:21.29,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,352)}Act 23\NEdmond Dantes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.98,0:23:21.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Edmond Dantes."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.91,0:23:24.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
